description: Russia enters the final day of its presidential election on March 17. President Vladimir Putin is certain to win, barring unexpected developments.
title: Russia’s Presidential Election 2024 Live: Candidates, polls and when results will be announced

description: Trucks of flour have reached northern Gaza for distribution to areas that have had no aid in four months, Palestinian media reported on Sunday, with famine looming in the enclave and truce talks between Israel and Hamas due to resume in Qatar.
title: Aid reaches northern Gaza as Israel and Hamas consider truce talks

description: British security firm Ambrey said on Sunday that it had received a report that a Yemeni fishing vessel had been hijacked in the Gulf of Aden.
title: Ambrey says has report of hijacked Yemeni fishing vessel in Gulf of Aden

description: Australia's Foreign Minister Penny Wong, the country's first openly gay female parliamentarian, has married her partner Sophie Allouache, Wong said on Sunday.
title: Australia Foreign Minister Penny Wong marries longtime partner

description: Residents in parts of Australia's Northern Territory and Queensland state were urged on Sunday to prepare for a tropical cyclone that is forecast to make landfall in coming days.
title: Australia's north braces for Tropical Cyclone Megan

description: South Ossetia, a region that broke away from Georgia and calls itself an independent state, has discussed becoming part of Russia with Moscow officials, Russian news agency RIA cited the head of South Ossetia's parliament as saying on Sunday.
title: Breakaway Georgian region is discussing becoming part of Russia, says local official

description: Colombia will suspend its months-long ceasefire with the Estado Mayor Central (ECM) armed group in three provinces on Wednesday, a government decree said on Sunday, citing incidents of violence that broke the ceasefire.
title: Colombia decree suspends ceasefire with EMC armed group in three areas

description: A traffic accident in southern Afghanistan killed 21 people and injured dozens on Sunday, the provincial government said.
title: Crash involving passenger bus, fuel truck kills 21 in Afghanistan

description: European leaders are expected to announce a multi-billion euro funding package and an upgraded relationship with Egypt in Cairo on Sunday, part of a push to stem migrant flows across the Mediterranean that has been criticised by rights groups.
title: EU to bolster Egypt ties with billions in funding

description: European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen said on Sunday that Gaza was facing famine and there had to be a rapid ceasefire agreement in the war between Israel and Hamas.
title: EU's von der Leyen says Gaza facing famine, ceasefire needed rapidly

description: The captain of a merchant ship east of Yemen's Aden has reported an explosion near the ship, the United Kingdom Maritime Trade Operations (UKMTO) agency said early on Sunday.
title: Explosion reported near ship off Yemen coast, UKMTO says

description: The large number of civilian casualties that would result from an Israeli assault on the Gaza city of Rafah would make regional peace "very difficult", German Chancellor Olaf Scholz said on Sunday after talks with Jordanian King Abdullah.
title: Germany's Scholz say Rafah assault would make regional peace 'very difficult'

description: India's "lottery king", accused by the authorities of fraud and money laundering, has emerged with his company as the nation's top political donor under an opaque funding system that has just been partially opened to scrutiny.
title: India's 'lottery king' emerges as top political donor in opaque system

description: Officials in Moldova's pro-Russian, separatist Transdniestria enclave said a drone launched from Ukraine's Odesa region blew up a helicopter on military territory on Sunday, local media said, but pro-European Moldova immediately dismissed the report.
title: Moldova dismisses reported drone strike in breakaway enclave as provocation

description: Yulia Navalnaya, the widow of Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny, took part in a noon protest against President Vladimir Putin on Sunday in Berlin.
title: Navalny's widow takes part in 'noon against Putin' protest in Berlin, activists say

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu told CNN on Sunday that U.S. Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer's speech in which he urged new elections in Israel was "totally inappropriate."
title: Netanyahu says Schumer speech calling for Israel election was inappropriate

description: Despite the protesters, who represent a fraction of Russia's 114 million voters, Vladimir Putin is poised to remain in power. If he completes his six-year term, he would overtake Josef Stalin to become Russia's longest-serving leader for more than 200 years.
title: 'Noon against Putin': thousands of Russians turn out to fulfil Navalny's 'last wish'

description: Vladimir Putin has won Russia's presidential election with 87.97% of the vote, according to the first official results showed on Sunday after polls closed.
title: Putin wins Russian presidential election with 87.97% of the vote, first official results show

description: Following are reactions from foreign governments and officials to Russia's presidential election, which handed Vladimir Putin a landslide win and another six-year term in office, according to first official results on Sunday.
title: Reactions abroad to Russia's presidential election

description: At least a thousand anti-Kremlin Russian emigres queued for hours outside their embassy in Armenia on Sunday, waiting to cast ballots in presidential election they admit they have little chance of influencing.
title: Russian emigres in Armenia stand in line to vote against Putin

description: Russian citizens in Latvia cast ballots in their home country's presidential election on Sunday, while opponents of President Vladimir Putin rallied in front of the embassy in Riga in a peaceful "noon against Putin" protest.
title: Russians in Latvia vote in presidential election, and some protest against Putin

description: Russian air attacks damaged agricultural enterprises and destroyed several industrial buildings in the Black Sea port of Odesa overnight, Ukraine's forces said on Sunday.
title: Russia's drone attack on Odesa damages agribusinesses, Ukraine says

description: The final day of the three-day election, which almost certainly will go to Vladimir Putin, will test the strength of the country's opposition, which called for its supporters to vote at the same time in an action dubbed, "Noon Against Putin."
title: Russia's presidential vote starts final day with accusations of Kyiv sabotage

description: Dozens of Russians flocked to Alexei Navalny's grave in Moscow on Sunday to symbolically cast their vote for the late opposition politician on the last day of Russia's presidential election, TV footage showed.
title: Some Russians flock to Navalny's grave to 'cast their vote,' TV footage shows

description: A far-right Austrian politician was stopped by the police from speaking at an event in the Swiss canton of Aargau on Saturday after the organisers didn't comply with a police request for the event to be cancelled.
title: Swiss police stop far-right Austrian politician speaking at event

description: Thousands of Russian citizens in Serbia and Montenegro voted on Sunday in their home nation's presidential election, with many saying it was a symbolic gesture that would not impact President Vladimir Putin's bid for another six-year term.
title: Thousands of Russians vote in Serbia, Montenegro, many say they oppose Putin

description: Ukraine launched several drones at the Slavyansk oil refinery in Russia's Krasnodar region, sparking a brief fire at the site and resulting in one person dying of a heart attack, local officials said on Sunday.
title: Ukraine drone attacks spark fire at Krasnodar refinery, Russia says

description: Ukraine reported dozens of attacks by Russia near their shared border on Sunday as partial results showed President Vladimir Putin winning reelection by the largest margin since Soviet times.
title: Ukraine says Russia attacks border regions as partial results show Putin reelection

description: At least six people were wounded in a Russian missile attack on the Black Sea port city of Mykolaiv on Sunday, Ukrainian officials said, after an overnight strike on the port of Odesa on the last day of Russia's presidential election.
title: Ukraine says Russian missile attack on Mykolaiv city injures 6

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said on Sunday that Russian President Vladimir Putin wanted to rule forever and that Russia's presidential election was an illegitimate imitation.
title: Ukraine's Zelenskiy says Russian elections illegitimate 'imitation'

description: Long-range Ukrainian attack drones launched by the SBU domestic security service have hit 12 Russian oil refineries during the war so far, a Ukrainian intelligence source told Reuters on Sunday.
title: Ukrainian drones have hit 12 Russian oil refineries, Kyiv source says

description: The U.N. children's agency said on Saturday one of its aid containers at Haiti's main port, stocked with "essential items for maternal, neonatal and child survival," was looted, as gangs increasingly control the capital.
title: UNICEF says essential aid container looted at Haiti port

description: The U.N. children's agency said on Sunday over 13,000 children have been killed in Gaza in Israel's offensive, adding many kids were suffering from severe malnutrition and did not "even have the energy to cry."
title: UNICEF says over 13,000 children killed in Gaza in Israel offensive

description: The U.S. military said it destroyed a drone fired by the Yemeni Houthis on Saturday, with another presumed to have crashed into the Red Sea.
title: US military says it destroyed Houthi drone over Red Sea

description: Vietnam's parliament is set to meet on Thursday to discuss unspecified "personnel issues", according to a letter sent to legislators seen by Reuters, amid speculation of a reshuffle of the Communist-ruled country's top leadership.
title: Vietnam's parliament to meet over 'personnel issues', says letter to legislators
